    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@digitalinformation It looks like you have downloaded the source distribution of Besu and not the binaries. On the releases page https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/releases the jfrog links have the binary distribution you need.\r\n\r\nThe directory structure should look like this.\r\n<img width=\"230\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-11-02 at 8 09 35 am\" src=\"https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/assets/909467/c66dcec4-cc52-4af3-b031-57ae1ea513d7\">\r\n\r\nThen you can run besu from the bin directory.\r\n\r\nre: docker question\r\nYou do need to create a directory. The directory is needed for the local database that Besu uses as it's copy of the blockchain. It's up to you where you create the directory but for the location you will need to have a large amount of disk space at least 650GB for mainnet https://besu.hyperledger.org/development/public-networks/concepts/data-storage-formats#storage-requirements.",
